Module not found: Error: Can't resolve 'App.js' in '/Users/xavgab/Worksplace/13_Projet 13/language_project/ludic_language/frontend/src/components'
Did you mean './App.js'?
Requests that should resolve in the current directory need to start with './'.
Requests that start with a name are treated as module requests and resolve within module directories (src, node_modules).
If changing the source code is not an option there is also a resolve options called 'preferRelative' which tries to resolve these kind of requests in the current directory too.
